==Trivia==
*In the comics, James Buchanan Barnes, named after the 15th President of the [[United States of America]], {{WPS|James Buchanan}}, had a complicated romantic relationship with [[Black Widow]], and took over the mantle of Captain America after [[Steve Rogers]] was assassinated by [[Crossbones]].
**In the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]], Barnes occasionally uses [[Captain America's Shield]], a reference to his role as [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]]'s successor in the comics.
*In the comics, the codename '''White Wolf''' is used by [[w:c:marvel:White Wolf|Hunter]], a foreigner adopted by [[T'Chaka]] who became an anti-hero and the head of the [[War Dogs|Hatut Zeraze]].
*Although his [[Winter Soldier's Prosthetic Arm|bionic arm]] is his left arm, Barnes is right-handed.
*In the VFX company Perception's [https://vimeo.com/111663225 extended Zola montage] for ''[[Captain America: The Winter Soldier]]'', Barnes is pictured holding a gun on a street in a photo dated [[2012|October 9, 2012]]. In real life, {{WPS|Malala Yousafzai}} was shot in the head on October 9, 2012 by an unidentified masked gunman who boarded her school bus and quickly fled the scene.
*Barnes weighs 182 lbs. and is 5'11,<ref name="Files"/> his height is also given as 6'0.<ref>[[:File:Winter Soldier Trading Card Back Promo.jpg|Bucky Barnes Trading Card]]</ref>

==Behind the Scenes==
*[[Ed Brubaker]], who co-created the Winter Soldier, appears in ''[[Captain America: The Winter Soldier]]'', as a Hydra doctor who helps repair the Winter Soldier's mechanical arm.
*[[Sebastian Stan]] was uncredited for his appearances in ''[[Ant-Man (film)|Ant-Man]]'' and ''[[Black Panther (film)|Black Panther]]''.
*[[James Young]], [[Jason Charles Hill]], [[Greg Rementer]], [[Jimmy N. Roberts]], [[Justin Sundquist]], [[Spencer Mulligan]], [[John Nania]], [[Nicolas Bosc]] and [[Kade Pittman]] were stunt doubles for [[Sebastian Stan]] in the role of Winter Soldier.
*[[Colin Botts]], [[Jared Leland Gore]] and [[Kirk Riley]] were stand-ins for [[Sebastian Stan]] in the role of Winter Soldier.

